item.title: Locating Jdk?
item.dc:creator: @Travas Travas
item.description:
@Travas wrote:

Look in your “Program Files” or “Program Files (x86)” for a folder called “Java”. Inside that Java folder should be a JDK folder. Get the Directory of the “bin” folder that is INSIDE the JDK folder, and place it in the right spot inside the compiler. You may also need to set environmental variables.

If you did not understand what I said, go here: http://www.moparisthebest.com/smf/index.php/topic,372873.0.html

Read full topic
